1 var App;
  2 App = {};var App;
  3 App = {};var App;
  4 App = {};;
  5 var Callback, Event, Guard, GuardsCollection, Machine, StateMachine, Transition;
  6 StateMachine = function(name, object, options, block) {
  7   return Machine(name, object, options, block);
  8 };
  9 Callback = function(options, machine, block) {
 10   var self;
 11   self = {
 12     match: function(from_state, to_state, event) {
 13       if (options.to && options.from) {
 14         if (options.to === to_state && options.from === from_state) {
 15           return true;
 16         }
 17         return false;
 18       }
 19       if ((options.to === to_state) || (options.from === from_state) || (options.on === event.name)) {
 20         return true;
 21       }
 22     },
 23     run: function(params) {
 24       (typeof block === "undefined" || block === null) ? undefined : block.apply(machine.object, params);
 25       return options.run ? options.run.apply(machine.object, params) : null;
 26     }
 27   };
 28   return self;
 29 };
 30 Event = function(name, machine) {
 31   var guards, self, transition_for;
 32   guards = GuardsCollection();
 33   transition_for = function(params) {
 34     var from, to;
 35     if (can_fire(params)) {
 36       from = machine.state();
 37       to = guards.find_to_state(name, from, params);
 38       return Transition(machine, self, from, to, params);
 39     } else {
 40       return false;
 41     }
 42   };
 43   self = {
 44     transition: function(options) {
 45       guards.add(name, machine.object, options);
 46       machine.states.push(options.from);
 47       machine.states.push(options.to);
 48       return self;
 49     },
 50     can_fire: function(params) {
 51       if (guards.match(name, machine.state(), params)) {
 52         return true;
 53       }
 54       return false;
 55     },
 56     fire: function(params) {
 57       var transition;
 58       transition = transition_for(params);
 59       if (transition) {
 60         return transition.perform();
 61       }
 62       return false;
 63     }
 64   };
 65   return self;
 66 };
 67 Guard = function(name, object, options) {
 68   var I, self;
 69   I = {
 70     from: options.from,
 71     to: options.to,
 72     except: options.except,
 73     options: options,
 74     name: name,
 75     object: object
 76   };
 77   self = {
 78     match: function(name, from, params) {
 79       if (name === I.name && match_from_state(I.from)) {
 80         if (run_callbacks(params)) {
 81           return true;
 82         }
 83       }
 84       return false;
 85     },
 86     match_from_state: function(from) {
 87       if (typeof I.from === 'string') {
 88         if (I.from === 'any') {
 89           return check_exceptions(from);
 90         } else {
 91           return from === I.from;
 92         }
 93       } else {
 94         return I.from.each(function(from_item) {
 95           if (from === from_item) {
 96             return true;
 97           }
 98           return false;
 99         });
100       }
101     },
102     check_exceptions: function(from) {
103       return from !== I.except;
104     },
105     run_callbacks: function(params) {
106       var success;
107       success = true;
108       if (I.options.when) {
109         success = I.options.when.apply(I.object, params);
110       }
111       if (I.options.unless && success) {
112         success = !I.options.unless.apply(I.object, params);
113       }
114       return success;
115     }
116   };
117   return self;
118 };
119 GuardsCollection = function() {
120   var guards, last_match, self;
121   guards = [];
122   last_match = null;
123   self = {
124     add: function(name, object, options) {
125       var guard;
126       guard = Guard(name, object, options);
127       guards.push(guard);
128       return guard;
129     },
130     all: function() {
131       return guards;
132     },
133     match: function(name, from, params) {
134       guards.each(function(guard) {
135         var match;
136         match = guard.match(name, from, params);
137         if (match) {
138           last_match = match;
139           return guard;
140         }
141       });
142       return false;
143     },
144     find_to_state: function(name, from, params) {
145       var local_match;
146       local_match = match(name, from, params);
147       if (local_match) {
148         return match.to;
149       }
150     }
151   };
152   return self;
153 };
154 Machine = function(name, object, options, block) {
155   var add_event_methods, add_methods_to_object, callbacks, events, internal_state, machine_name, self, set_state, states;
156   events = [];
157   states = [];
158   callbacks = {
159     before: [],
160     after: []
161   };
162   machine_name = name;
163   internal_state = options && (options.initial ? options.initial : '');
164   add_methods_to_object(name, object);
165   if (block) {
166     block(self);
167   }
168   return self;
169   add_methods_to_object = function(name, object) {
170     object[name] = self.state();
171     object[name + '_events'] = events;
172     return (object[name + '_states'] = states);
173   };
174   add_event_methods = function(name, object, event) {
175     object[name] = function() {
176       return event.fire(arguments);
177     };
178     return (object['can_' + name] = function() {
179       return event.can_fire();
180     });
181   };
182   set_state = function(state) {
183     internal_state = state;
184     return (object[machine_name] = state);
185   };
186   return (self = {
187     event: function(name, block) {
188       var event;
189       event = Event(name, self);
190       events.push(event);
191       add_event_methods(name, object, event);
192       if (block) {
193         block(event);
194       }
195       return event;
196     },
197     before_transition: function(options, block) {
198       var callback;
199       callback = Callback(options, self, block);
200       callbacks["before"].push(callback);
201       return callback;
202     },
203     after_transition: function(options, block) {
204       var callback;
205       callback = Callback(options, self, block);
206       callbacks["after"].push(callback);
207       return callback;
208     },
209     state: function() {
210       return internal_state;
211     }
212   });
213 };
214 Transition = function(machine, event, from, to, params) {
215   var self;
216   return (self = {
217     perform: function() {
218       self.before();
219       machine.set_state(to);
220       self.after();
221       return true;
222     },
223     before: function() {
224       return machine.callbacks['before'].each(function(callback) {
225         return callback.match(from, to, event) ? callback.run(params) : null;
226       });
227     },
228     after: function() {
229       return machine.callbacks['after'].each(function(callback) {
230         return callback.match(from, to, event) ? callback.run(params) : null;
231       });
232     },
233     rollback: function() {
234       return machine.set_state(from);
235     }
236   });
237 };;
238 /**
239 * Creates and returns a copy of the array. The copy contains
240 * the same objects.
241 *
242 * @type Array
243 * @returns A new array that is a copy of the array
244 */
245 Array.prototype.copy = function() {
246   return this.concat();  
247 };

249 /**
250 * Empties the array of its contents. It is modified in place.
251 *
252 * @type Array
253 * @returns this, now emptied.
254 */
255 Array.prototype.clear = function() {
256   this.length = 0;
257   return this;
258 };

260 /**
261 * Invoke the named method on each element in the array
262 * and return a new array containing the results of the invocation.
263 *
264 <code><pre>
265   [1.1, 2.2, 3.3, 4.4].invoke("floor")
266   => [1, 2, 3, 4]
267 
268   ['hello', 'world', 'cool!'].invoke('substring', 0, 3)
269   => ['hel', 'wor', 'coo']
270 </pre></code>
271 *
272 * @param {String} method The name of the method to invoke.
273 * @param [arg...] Optional arguments to pass to the method being invoked.
274 *
275 * @type Array
276 * @returns A new array containing the results of invoking the 
277 * named method on each element.
278 */
279 Array.prototype.invoke = function(method) {
280   var args = Array.prototype.slice.call(arguments, 1);
281   
282   return this.map(function(element) {
283     return element[method].apply(element, args);
284   });
285 };

287 /**
288 * Randomly select an element from the array.
289 *
290 * @returns A random element from an array
291 */
292 Array.prototype.rand = function() {
293   return this[rand(this.length)];
294 };
295 
296 /**
297 * Remove the first occurance of the given object from the array if it is
298 * present.
299 *
300 * @param {Object} object The object to remove from the array if present.
301 * @returns The removed object if present otherwise undefined.
302 */
303 Array.prototype.remove = function(object) {
304   var index = this.indexOf(object);
305   if(index >= 0) {
306     return this.splice(index, 1)[0];
307   } else {
308     return undefined;
309   }
310 };
311 
312 /**
313 * Returns true if the element is present in the array.
314 *
315 * @param {Object} element The element to check if present.
316 * @returns true if the element is in the array, false otherwise.
317 * @type Boolean
318 */
319 Array.prototype.include = function(element) {
320   return this.indexOf(element) != -1;
321 };
322 
323 /**
324  * Call the given iterator once for each element in the array,
325  * passing in the element as the first argument, the index of 
326  * the element as the second argument, and this array as the
327  * third argument.
328  *
329  * @param {Function} iterator Function to be called once for 
330  * each element in the array.
331  * @param {Object} [context] Optional context parameter to be 
332  * used as `this` when calling the iterator function.
333  *
334  * @returns `this` to enable method chaining.
335  */
336 Array.prototype.each = function(iterator, context) {
337   if(this.forEach) {
338     this.forEach(iterator, context);
339   } else {
340     var len = this.length;
341     for(var i = 0; i < len; i++) {
342       iterator.call(context, this[i], i, this);
343     }
344   }
345 
346   return this;
347 };
348 
349 Array.prototype.eachSlice = function(n, iterator, context) {
350   var len = Math.floor(this.length / n);
351   
352   for(var i = 0; i < len; i++) {
353     iterator.call(context, this.slice(i*n, (i+1)*n), i*n, this);
354   }
355   
356   return this;
357 };
358 
359 /**
360  * Returns a new array with the elements all shuffled up.
361  *
362  * @returns A new array that is randomly shuffled.
363  * @type Array
364  */
365 Array.prototype.shuffle = function() {
366   var shuffledArray = [];
367   
368   this.each(function(element) {
369     shuffledArray.splice(rand(shuffledArray.length + 1), 0, element);
370   });
371   
372   return shuffledArray;
373 };

375 /**
376  * Returns the first element of the array, undefined if the array is empty.
377  *
378  * @returns The first element, or undefined if the array is empty.
379  * @type Object
380  */
381 Array.prototype.first = function() {
382   return this[0];
383 };
384 
385 /**
386  * Returns the last element of the array, undefined if the array is empty.
387  *
388  * @returns The last element, or undefined if the array is empty.
389  * @type Object
390  */
391 Array.prototype.last = function() {
392   return this[this.length - 1];
393 };
394 
395 /**
396  * Pretend the array is a circle and grab a new array containing length elements. 
397  * If length is not given return the element at start, again assuming the array 
398  * is a circle.
399  *
400  * @param {Number} start The index to start wrapping at, or the index of the 
401  * sole element to return if no length is given.
402  * @param {Number} [length] Optional length determines how long result 
403  * array should be.
404  * @returns The element at start mod array.length, or an array of length elements, 
405  * starting from start and wrapping.
406  * @type Object or Array
407  */
408 Array.prototype.wrap = function(start, length) {
409   if(length != null) {
410     var end = start + length;
411     var result = [];
412   
413     for(var i = start; i < end; i++) {
414       result.push(this[i.mod(this.length)]);
415     }
416   
417     return result;
418   } else {
419     return this[start.mod(this.length)];
420   }
421 };
422 
423 /**
424  * Partitions the elements into two groups: those for which the iterator returns
425  * true, and those for which it returns false.
426  * @param {Function} iterator
427  * @param {Object} [context] Optional context parameter to be
428  * used as `this` when calling the iterator function.
429  *
430  * @type Array
431  * @returns An array in the form of [trueCollection, falseCollection]
432  */
433 Array.prototype.partition = function(iterator, context) {
434   var trueCollection = [];
435   var falseCollection = [];
436 
437   this.each(function(element) {
438     if(iterator.call(context, element)) {
439       trueCollection.push(element);
440     } else {
441       falseCollection.push(element);
442     }
443   });
444 
445   return [trueCollection, falseCollection];
446 };
447 
448 /**
449  * Return the group of elements for which the iterator's return value is true.
450  * 
451  * @param {Function} iterator The iterator receives each element in turn as 
452  * the first agument.
453  * @param {Object} [context] Optional context parameter to be
454  * used as `this` when calling the iterator function.
455  *
456  * @type Array
457  * @returns An array containing the elements for which the iterator returned true.
458  */
459 Array.prototype.select = function(iterator, context) {
460   return this.partition(iterator, context)[0];
461 };
462 
463 /**
464  * Return the group of elements that are not in the passed in set.
465  * 
466  * @param {Array} values List of elements to exclude.
467  *
468  * @type Array
469  * @returns An array containing the elements that are not passed in.
470  */
471 Array.prototype.without = function(values) {
472   return this.reject(function(element) {
473     return values.include(element);
474   });
475 };
476 
477 /**
478  * Return the group of elements for which the iterator's return value is false.
479  * 
480  * @param {Function} iterator The iterator receives each element in turn as 
481  * the first agument.
482  * @param {Object} [context] Optional context parameter to be
483  * used as `this` when calling the iterator function.
484  *
485  * @type Array
486  * @returns An array containing the elements for which the iterator returned false.
487  */
488 Array.prototype.reject = function(iterator, context) {
489   return this.partition(iterator, context)[1];
490 };
491 
492 Array.prototype.inject = function(initial, iterator) {
493   this.each(function(element) {
494     initial = iterator(initial, element);
495   });
496   
497   return initial;
498 };
499 
500 Array.prototype.sum = function() {
501   return this.inject(0, function(sum, n) {
502     return sum + n;
503   });
504 };

644 var Core;
645 var __slice = Array.prototype.slice;
646 /**
647 The Core class is used to add extended functionality to objects without
648 extending the object class directly. Inherit from Core to gain its utility
649 methods.
650 
651 @name Core
652 @constructor
653 
654 @param {Object} I Instance variables
655 */
656 Core = function(I) {
657   var self;
658   I || (I = {});
659   return (self = {
660     I: I,
661     /**
662     Generates a public jQuery style getter / setter method for each
663     String argument.
664 
665     @name attrAccessor
666     @methodOf Core#
667     */
668     attrAccessor: function() {
669       var attrNames;
670       attrNames = __slice.call(arguments, 0);
671       return attrNames.each(function(attrName) {
672         return (self[attrName] = function(newValue) {
673           if (typeof newValue !== "undefined" && newValue !== null) {
674             I[attrName] = newValue;
675             return self;
676           } else {
677             return I[attrName];
678           }
679         });
680       });
681     },
682     /**
683     Generates a public jQuery style getter method for each String argument.
684 
685     @name attrReader
686     @methodOf Core#
687     */
688     attrReader: function() {
689       var attrNames;
690       attrNames = __slice.call(arguments, 0);
691       return attrNames.each(function(attrName) {
692         return (self[attrName] = function() {
693           return I[attrName];
694         });
695       });
696     },
697     /**
698     Extends this object with methods from the passed in object. `before` and
699     `after` are special option names that glue functionality before or after
700     existing methods.
701 
702     @name extend
703     @methodOf Core#
704     */
705     extend: function(options) {
706       var afterMethods, beforeMethods;
707       afterMethods = options.after;
708       beforeMethods = options.before;
709       delete options.after;
710       delete options.before;
711       $.extend(self, options);
712       if (beforeMethods) {
713         $.each(beforeMethods, function(name, fn) {
714           return (self[name] = self[name].withBefore(fn));
715         });
716       }
717       if (afterMethods) {
718         $.each(afterMethods, function(name, fn) {
719           return (self[name] = self[name].withAfter(fn));
720         });
721       }
722       return self;
723     },
724     include: function(Module) {
725       return self.extend(Module(I, self));
726     }
727   });
728 };;
729 var DebugConsole;
730 DebugConsole = function() {
731   var REPL, container, input, output, repl, runButton;
732   REPL = function(input, output) {
733     var print;
734     print = function(message) {
735       return output.append($("<li />", {
736         text: message
737       }));
738     };
739     return {
740       run: function() {
741         var code, result, source;
742         source = input.val();
743         try {
744           code = CoffeeScript.compile(source, {
745             noWrap: true
746           });
747           result = eval(code);
748           print(" => " + (result));
749           return input.val('');
750         } catch (error) {
751           return error.stack ? print(error.stack) : print(error.toString());
752         }
753       }
754     };
755   };
756   container = $("<div />", {
757     "class": "console"
758   });
759   input = $("<textarea />");
760   output = $("<ul />");
761   runButton = $("<button />", {
762     text: "Run"
763   });
764   repl = REPL(input, output);
765   container.append(output).append(input).append(runButton);
766   return $(function() {
767     runButton.click(function() {
768       return repl.run();
769     });
770     return $("body").append(container);
771   });
772 };;
773 Function.prototype.withBefore = function(interception) {
774   var method;
775   method = this;
776   return function() {
777     interception.apply(this, arguments);
778     return method.apply(this, arguments);
779   };
780 };
781 Function.prototype.withAfter = function(interception) {
782   var method;
783   method = this;
784   return function() {
785     var result;
786     result = method.apply(this, arguments);
787     interception.apply(this, arguments);
788     return result;
789   };
790 };;

825   function keyHandler( handleObj ) {
826     // Only care when a possible input has been specified
827     if ( typeof handleObj.data !== "string" ) {
828       return;
829     }
830     
831     var origHandler = handleObj.handler,
832       keys = handleObj.data.toLowerCase().split(" ");
833   
834     handleObj.handler = function( event ) {
835       // Don't fire in text-accepting inputs that we didn't directly bind to
836       if ( this !== event.target && (/textarea|select/i.test( event.target.nodeName ) ||
837          event.target.type === "text" || event.target.type === "password") ) {
838         return;
839       }
840       
841       // Keypress represents characters, not special keys
842       var special = event.type !== "keypress" && jQuery.hotkeys.specialKeys[ event.which ],
843         character = String.fromCharCode( event.which ).toLowerCase(),
844         key, modif = "", possible = {};
845 
846       // check combinations (alt|ctrl|shift+anything)
847       if ( event.altKey && special !== "alt" ) {
848         modif += "alt+";
849       }
850 
851       if ( event.ctrlKey && special !== "ctrl" ) {
852         modif += "ctrl+";
853       }
854       
855       // TODO: Need to make sure this works consistently across platforms
856       if ( event.metaKey && !event.ctrlKey && special !== "meta" ) {
857         modif += "meta+";
858       }
859 
860       if ( event.shiftKey && special !== "shift" ) {
861         modif += "shift+";
862       }
863 
864       if ( special ) {
865         possible[ modif + special ] = true;
866 
867       } else {
868         possible[ modif + character ] = true;
869         possible[ modif + jQuery.hotkeys.shiftNums[ character ] ] = true;
870 
871         // "$" can be triggered as "Shift+4" or "Shift+$" or just "$"
872         if ( modif === "shift+" ) {
873           possible[ jQuery.hotkeys.shiftNums[ character ] ] = true;
874         }
875       }
876 
877       for ( var i = 0, l = keys.length; i < l; i++ ) {
878         if ( possible[ keys[i] ] ) {
879           return origHandler.apply( this, arguments );
880         }
881       }
882     };
883   }
884 
885   jQuery.each([ "keydown", "keyup", "keypress" ], function() {
886     jQuery.event.special[ this ] = { add: keyHandler };
887   });

890 /**
891  * Merges properties from objects into target without overiding.
892  * First come, first served.
893  * @return target
894  */
895 jQuery.extend({
896   reverseMerge: function(target) {
897     var i = 1, length = arguments.length;
898 
899     for( ; i < length; i++) {
900       var object = arguments[i];
901 
902       for(var name in object) {
903         if(!target.hasOwnProperty(name)) {
904           target[name] = object[name];
905         }
906       }
907     }
908 
909     return target;
910   }

971 (function() {
972   /**
973    * Create a new point with given x and y coordinates. If no arguments are given
974    * defaults to (0, 0).
975    * @name Point
976    * @param {Number} [x]
977    * @param {Number} [y]
978    * @constructor
979    */
980   function Point(x, y) {
981     return {
982       /**
983        * The x coordinate of this point.
984        * @name x
985        * @fieldOf Point#
986        */
987       x: x || 0,
988       /**
989        * The y coordinate of this point.
990        * @name y
991        * @fieldOf Point#
992        */
993       y: y || 0,
994       /**
995        * Adds a point to this one and returns the new point.
996        * @name add
997        * @methodOf Point#
998        *
999        * @param {Point} other The point to add this point to.
1000        * @returns A new point, the sum of both.
1001        * @type Point
1002        */
1003       add: function(other) {
1004         return Point(this.x + other.x, this.y + other.y);
1005       },
1006       /**
1007        * Subtracts a point to this one and returns the new point.
1008        * @name subtract
1009        * @methodOf Point#
1010        *
1011        * @param {Point} other The point to subtract from this point.
1012        * @returns A new point, this - other.
1013        * @type Point
1014        */
1015       subtract: function(other) {
1016         return Point(this.x - other.x, this.y - other.y);
1017       },
1018       /**
1019        * Scale this Point (Vector) by a constant amount.
1020        * @name scale
1021        * @methodOf Point#
1022        *
1023        * @param {Number} scalar The amount to scale this point by.
1024        * @returns A new point, this * scalar.
1025        * @type Point
1026        */
1027       scale: function(scalar) {
1028         return Point(this.x * scalar, this.y * scalar);
1029       },
1030       /**
1031        * Determine whether this point is equal to another point.
1032        * @name equal
1033        * @methodOf Point#
1034        *
1035        * @param {Point} other The point to check for equality.
1036        * @returns true if the other point has the same x, y coordinates, false otherwise.
1037        * @type Boolean
1038        */
1039       equal: function(other) {
1040         return this.x === other.x && this.y === other.y;
1041       },
1042       /**
1043        * Calculate the magnitude of this Point (Vector).
1044        * @name magnitude
1045        * @methodOf Point#
1046        *
1047        * @returns The magnitude of this point as if it were a vector from (0, 0) -> (x, y).
1048        * @type Number
1049        */
1050       magnitude: function() {
1051         return Point.distance(Point(0, 0), this);
1052       },
1053       /**
1054        * Calculate the dot product of this point and another point (Vector).
1055        * @name dot
1056        * @methodOf Point#
1057        *
1058        * @param {Point} other The point to dot with this point.
1059        * @returns The dot product of this point dot other as a scalar value.
1060        * @type Number
1061        */
1062       dot: function(other) {
1063         return this.x * other.x + this.y * other.y;
1064       },
1065       /**
1066        * Calculate the cross product of this point and another point (Vector). 
1067        * Usually cross products are thought of as only applying to three dimensional vectors,
1068        * but z can be treated as zero. The result of this method is interpreted as the magnitude 
1069        * of the vector result of the cross product between [x1, y1, 0] x [x2, y2, 0]
1070        * perpendicular to the xy plane.
1071        * @name cross
1072        * @methodOf Point#
1073        *
1074        * @param {Point} other The point to cross with this point.
1075        * @returns The cross product of this point with the other point as scalar value.
1076        * @type Number
1077        */
1078       cross: function(other) {
1079         return this.x * other.y - other.x * this.y;
1080       },
1081       /**
1082        * The norm of a vector is the unit vector pointing in the same direction. This method
1083        * treats the point as though it is a vector from the origin to (x, y).
1084        * @name norm
1085        * @methodOf Point#
1086        *
1087        * @returns The unit vector pointing in the same direction as this vector.
1088        * @type Point
1089        */
1090       norm: function() {
1091         return this.scale(1.0/this.length());
1092       },
1093       /**
1094        * Computed the length of this point as though it were a vector from (0,0) to (x,y)
1095        * @name length
1096        * @methodOf Point#
1097        *
1098        * @returns The length of the vector from the origin to this point.
1099        * @type Number
1100        */
1101       length: function() {
1102         return Math.sqrt(this.dot(this));
1103       },
1104       /**
1105        * Computed the Euclidean between this point and another point.
1106        * @name distance
1107        * @methodOf Point#
1108        *
1109        * @param {Point} other The point to compute the distance to.
1110        * @returns The distance between this point and another point.
1111        * @type Number
1112        */
1113       distance: function(other) {
1114         return Point.distance(this, other);
1115       }
1116     }
1117   }
1118 
1119   /**
1120    * @param {Point} p1
1121    * @param {Point} p2
1122    * @type Number
1123    * @returns The Euclidean distance between two points.
1124    */
1125   Point.distance = function(p1, p2) {
1126     return Math.sqrt(Math.pow(p2.x - p1.x, 2) + Math.pow(p2.y - p1.y, 2));
1127   };
1128 
1129   /**
1130    * Construct a point on the unit circle for the given angle.
1131    *
1132    * @param {Number} angle The angle in radians
1133    * @type Point
1134    * @returns The point on the unit circle.
1135    */
1136   Point.fromAngle = function(angle) {
1137     return Point(Math.cos(angle), Math.sin(angle));
1138   };

1140   /**
1141    * If you have two dudes, one standing at point p1, and the other
1142    * standing at point p2, then this method will return the direction
1143    * that the dude standing at p1 will need to face to look at p2.
1144    * @param {Point} p1 The starting point.
1145    * @param {Point} p2 The ending point.
1146    * @returns The direction from p1 to p2 in radians.
1147    */
1148   Point.direction = function(p1, p2) {
1149     return Math.atan2(
1150       p2.y - p1.y,
1151       p2.x - p1.x
1152     );
1153   };
1154 
1155   /**
1156    * <pre>
1157    *  _        _
1158    * | a  c tx  |
1159    * | b  d ty  |
1160    * |_0  0  1 _|
1161    * </pre>
1162    * Creates a matrix for 2d affine transformations.
1163    *
1164    * concat, inverse, rotate, scale and translate return new matrices with the
1165    * transformations applied. The matrix is not modified in place.
1166    *
1167    * Returns the identity matrix when called with no arguments.
1168    * @name Matrix
1169    * @param {Number} [a]
1170    * @param {Number} [b]
1171    * @param {Number} [c]
1172    * @param {Number} [d]
1173    * @param {Number} [tx]
1174    * @param {Number} [ty]
1175    * @constructor
1176    */
1177   function Matrix(a, b, c, d, tx, ty) {
1178     a = a !== undefined ? a : 1;
1179     d = d !== undefined ? d : 1;
1180 
1181     return {
1182       /**
1183        * @name a
1184        * @fieldOf Matrix#
1185        */
1186       a: a,
1187       /**
1188        * @name b
1189        * @fieldOf Matrix#
1190        */
1191       b: b || 0,
1192       /**
1193        * @name c
1194        * @fieldOf Matrix#
1195        */
1196       c: c || 0,
1197       /**
1198        * @name d
1199        * @fieldOf Matrix#
1200        */
1201       d: d,
1202       /**
1203        * @name tx
1204        * @fieldOf Matrix#
1205        */
1206       tx: tx || 0,
1207       /**
1208        * @name ty
1209        * @fieldOf Matrix#
1210        */
1211       ty: ty || 0,
1212 
1213       /**
1214        * Returns the result of this matrix multiplied by another matrix
1215        * combining the geometric effects of the two. In mathematical terms, 
1216        * concatenating two matrixes is the same as combining them using matrix multiplication.
1217        * If this matrix is A and the matrix passed in is B, the resulting matrix is A x B
1218        * http://mathworld.wolfram.com/MatrixMultiplication.html
1219        * @name concat
1220        * @methodOf Matrix#
1221        *
1222        * @param {Matrix} matrix The matrix to multiply this matrix by.
1223        * @returns The result of the matrix multiplication, a new matrix.
1224        * @type Matrix
1225        */
1226       concat: function(matrix) {
1227         return Matrix(
1228           this.a * matrix.a + this.c * matrix.b,
1229           this.b * matrix.a + this.d * matrix.b,
1230           this.a * matrix.c + this.c * matrix.d,
1231           this.b * matrix.c + this.d * matrix.d,
1232           this.a * matrix.tx + this.c * matrix.ty + this.tx,
1233           this.b * matrix.tx + this.d * matrix.ty + this.ty
1234         );
1235       },
1236 
1237       /**
1238        * Given a point in the pretransform coordinate space, returns the coordinates of 
1239        * that point after the transformation occurs. Unlike the standard transformation 
1240        * applied using the transformPoint() method, the deltaTransformPoint() method's 
1241        * transformation does not consider the translation parameters tx and ty.
1242        * @name deltaTransformPoint
1243        * @methodOf Matrix#
1244        * @see #transformPoint
1245        *
1246        * @return A new point transformed by this matrix ignoring tx and ty.
1247        * @type Point
1248        */
1249       deltaTransformPoint: function(point) {
1250         return Point(
1251           this.a * point.x + this.c * point.y,
1252           this.b * point.x + this.d * point.y
1253         );
1254       },
1255 
1256       /**
1257        * Returns the inverse of the matrix.
1258        * http://mathworld.wolfram.com/MatrixInverse.html
1259        * @name inverse
1260        * @methodOf Matrix#
1261        *
1262        * @returns A new matrix that is the inverse of this matrix.
1263        * @type Matrix
1264        */
1265       inverse: function() {
1266         var determinant = this.a * this.d - this.b * this.c;
1267         return Matrix(
1268           this.d / determinant,
1269           -this.b / determinant,
1270           -this.c / determinant,
1271           this.a / determinant,
1272           (this.c * this.ty - this.d * this.tx) / determinant,
1273           (this.b * this.tx - this.a * this.ty) / determinant
1274         );
1275       },
1276 
1277       /**
1278        * Returns a new matrix that corresponds this matrix multiplied by a
1279        * a rotation matrix.
1280        * @name rotate
1281        * @methodOf Matrix#
1282        * @see Matrix.rotation
1283        *
1284        * @param {Number} theta Amount to rotate in radians.
1285        * @param {Point} [aboutPoint] The point about which this rotation occurs. Defaults to (0,0).
1286        * @returns A new matrix, rotated by the specified amount.
1287        * @type Matrix
1288        */
1289       rotate: function(theta, aboutPoint) {
1290         return this.concat(Matrix.rotation(theta, aboutPoint));
1291       },
1292 
1293       /**
1294        * Returns a new matrix that corresponds this matrix multiplied by a
1295        * a scaling matrix.
1296        * @name scale
1297        * @methodOf Matrix#
1298        * @see Matrix.scale
1299        *
1300        * @param {Number} sx
1301        * @param {Number} [sy]
1302        * @param {Point} [aboutPoint] The point that remains fixed during the scaling
1303        * @type Matrix
1304        */
1305       scale: function(sx, sy, aboutPoint) {
1306         return this.concat(Matrix.scale(sx, sy, aboutPoint));
1307       },
1308 
1309       /**
1310        * Returns the result of applying the geometric transformation represented by the 
1311        * Matrix object to the specified point.
1312        * @name transformPoint
1313        * @methodOf Matrix#
1314        * @see #deltaTransformPoint
1315        *
1316        * @returns A new point with the transformation applied.
1317        * @type Point
1318        */
1319       transformPoint: function(point) {
1320         return Point(
1321           this.a * point.x + this.c * point.y + this.tx,
1322           this.b * point.x + this.d * point.y + this.ty
1323         );
1324       },
1325 
1326       /**
1327        * Translates the matrix along the x and y axes, as specified by the tx and ty parameters.
1328        * @name translate
1329        * @methodOf Matrix#
1330        * @see Matrix.translation
1331        *
1332        * @param {Number} tx The translation along the x axis.
1333        * @param {Number} ty The translation along the y axis.
1334        * @returns A new matrix with the translation applied.
1335        * @type Matrix
1336        */
1337       translate: function(tx, ty) {
1338         return this.concat(Matrix.translation(tx, ty));
1339       }
1340     }
1341   }
1342 
1343   /**
1344    * Creates a matrix transformation that corresponds to the given rotation,
1345    * around (0,0) or the specified point.
1346    * @see Matrix#rotate
1347    *
1348    * @param {Number} theta Rotation in radians.
1349    * @param {Point} [aboutPoint] The point about which this rotation occurs. Defaults to (0,0).
1350    * @returns 
1351    * @type Matrix
1352    */
1353   Matrix.rotation = function(theta, aboutPoint) {
1354     var rotationMatrix = Matrix(
1355       Math.cos(theta),
1356       Math.sin(theta),
1357       -Math.sin(theta),
1358       Math.cos(theta)
1359     );
1360 
1361     if(aboutPoint) {
1362       rotationMatrix =
1363         Matrix.translation(aboutPoint.x, aboutPoint.y).concat(
1364           rotationMatrix
1365         ).concat(
1366           Matrix.translation(-aboutPoint.x, -aboutPoint.y)
1367         );
1368     }
1369 
1370     return rotationMatrix;
1371   };
1372 
1373   /**
1374    * Returns a matrix that corresponds to scaling by factors of sx, sy along
1375    * the x and y axis respectively.
1376    * If only one parameter is given the matrix is scaled uniformly along both axis.
1377    * If the optional aboutPoint parameter is given the scaling takes place
1378    * about the given point.
1379    * @see Matrix#scale
1380    *
1381    * @param {Number} sx The amount to scale by along the x axis or uniformly if no sy is given.
1382    * @param {Number} [sy] The amount to scale by along the y axis.
1383    * @param {Point} [aboutPoint] The point about which the scaling occurs. Defaults to (0,0).
1384    * @returns A matrix transformation representing scaling by sx and sy.
1385    * @type Matrix
1386    */
1387   Matrix.scale = function(sx, sy, aboutPoint) {
1388     sy = sy || sx;
1389 
1390     var scaleMatrix = Matrix(sx, 0, 0, sy);
1391 
1392     if(aboutPoint) {
1393       scaleMatrix =
1394         Matrix.translation(aboutPoint.x, aboutPoint.y).concat(
1395           scaleMatrix
1396         ).concat(
1397           Matrix.translation(-aboutPoint.x, -aboutPoint.y)
1398         );
1399     }
1400 
1401     return scaleMatrix;
1402   };
1403 
1404   /**
1405    * Returns a matrix that corresponds to a translation of tx, ty.
1406    * @see Matrix#translate
1407    *
1408    * @param {Number} tx The amount to translate in the x direction.
1409    * @param {Number} ty The amount to translate in the y direction.
1410    * @return A matrix transformation representing a translation by tx and ty.
1411    * @type Matrix
1412    */
1413   Matrix.translation = function(tx, ty) {
1414     return Matrix(1, 0, 0, 1, tx, ty);
1415   };
1416 
1417   /**
1418    * A constant representing the identity matrix.
1419    * @name IDENTITY
1420    * @fieldOf Matrix
1421    */
1422   Matrix.IDENTITY = Matrix();
1423   /**
1424    * A constant representing the horizontal flip transformation matrix.
1425    * @name HORIZONTAL_FLIP
1426    * @fieldOf Matrix
1427    */
1428   Matrix.HORIZONTAL_FLIP = Matrix(-1, 0, 0, 1);
1429   /**
1430    * A constant representing the vertical flip transformation matrix.
1431    * @name VERTICAL_FLIP
1432    * @fieldOf Matrix
1433    */
1434   Matrix.VERTICAL_FLIP = Matrix(1, 0, 0, -1);
1435

1437   window["Point"] = Point;
1438   window["Matrix"] = Matrix;

1517 /**
1518  * A mod method useful for array wrapping. The range of the function is
1519  * constrained to remain in bounds of array indices.
1520  *
1521  * <pre>
1522  * Example:
1523  * (-1).mod(5) === 4
1524  * </pre>
1525  *
1526  * @param {Number} base
1527  * @returns An integer between 0 and (base - 1) if base is positive.
1528  * @type Number
1529  */
1530 Number.prototype.mod = function(base) {
1531   var result = this % base;
1532 
1533   if(result < 0 && base > 0) {
1534     result += base;
1535   }
1536 
1537   return result;
1538 };

1563 /**

1577     iterator.call(context, i);

2076   /**
2077   * Bindable module
2078   * @name Bindable
2079   * @constructor
2080   */
2081   function Bindable() {
2082     
2083     var eventCallbacks = {};
2084     
2085     return {
2086       /**
2087       * The bind method adds a function as an event listener.
2088       *
2089       * @name bind
2090       * @methodOf Bindable#
2091       *
2092       * @param {String} event The event to listen to.
2093       * @param {Function} callback The function to be called when the specified event
2094       * is triggered.
2095       */
2096       bind: function(event, callback) {
2097         eventCallbacks[event] = eventCallbacks[event] || [];
2098         
2099         eventCallbacks[event].push(callback);
2100       },
2101       
2102       unbind: function(event, callback) {
2103         eventCallbacks[event] = eventCallbacks[event] || [];
2104         
2105         if(callback) {
2106           eventCallbacks.remove(callback);
2107         } else {
2108           eventCallbacks[event] = [];
2109         }
2110       },
2111       /**
2112       * The trigger method calls all listeners attached to the specified event.
2113       *
2114       * @name trigger
2115       * @methodOf Bindable#
2116       *
2117       * @param {String} event The event to trigger.
2118       * @param {Array} [extraParameters] Additional parameters to pass to the event listener.
2119       */
2120       trigger: function(event, extraParameters) {
2121         var callbacks = eventCallbacks[event];
2122         
2123         if(callbacks && callbacks.length) {
2124           var self = this;
2125           $.each(callbacks, function(i, callback) {
2126             callback.apply(self, [self].concat(extraParameters));
2127           });
2128         }
2129       },
2130     };
2131   }
2132   
2133   window.Bindable = Bindable;

2193 var CellularAutomata;
2194 CellularAutomata = function(I) {
2195   var currentState, get, neighbors, nextState, self;
2196   I || (I = {});
2197   $.reverseMerge(I, {
2198     cellUpdate: function(row, col, value, neighbors) {
2199       var neighborCounts;
2200       neighborCounts = neighbors.sum();
2201       return +((value + neighborCounts) >= 5);
2202     },
2203     initializeCell: function(row, col) {
2204       return rand() < 0.45;
2205     },
2206     outsideValue: function(row, col) {
2207       return 1;
2208     },
2209     width: 32,
2210     height: 32
2211   });
2212   currentState = [];
2213   nextState = [];
2214   get = function(row, col) {
2215     if (((0 <= row) && (row < I.height)) && ((0 <= col) && (col < I.width))) {
2216       return currentState[row][col];
2217     } else {
2218       return I.outsideValue(row, col);
2219     }
2220   };
2221   neighbors = function(row, col) {
2222     return [get(row - 1, col - 1), get(row - 1, col), get(row - 1, col + 1), get(row, col - 1), get(row, col + 1), get(row + 1, col - 1), get(row + 1, col), get(row + 1, col + 1)];
2223   };
2224   I.height.times(function(row) {
2225     currentState[row] = [];
2226     return I.width.times(function(col) {
2227       return (currentState[row][col] = I.initializeCell(row, col));
2228     });
2229   });
2230   self = {
2231     data: function() {
2232       return currentState;
2233     },
2234     get: function(row, col) {
2235       return currentState[row][col];
2236     },
2237     update: function(updateFn) {
2238       I.height.times(function(row) {
2239         return (nextState[row] = currentState[row].map(function(value, col) {
2240           return updateFn ? updateFn(row, col, value, neighbors(row, col)) : I.cellUpdate(row, col, value, neighbors(row, col));
2241         }));
2242       });
2243       currentState = nextState;
2244       return (nextState = []);
2245     }
2246   };

2263 var Collision;
2264 Collision = {
2265   rectangular: function(a, b) {
2266     return a.x < b.x + b.width && a.x + a.width > b.x && a.y < b.y + b.height && a.y + a.height > b.y;
2267   },
2268   rayRectangle: function(source, direction, target) {
2269     var areaPQ0, areaPQ1, hit, p0, p1, t, tX, tY, xval, xw, yval, yw;
2270     xw = target.xw;
2271     yw = target.yw;
2272     if (source.x < target.x) {
2273       xval = target.x - xw;
2274     } else {
2275       xval = target.x + xw;
2276     }
2277     if (source.y < target.y) {
2278       yval = target.y - yw;
2279     } else {
2280       yval = target.y + yw;
2281     }
2282     if (direction.x === 0) {
2283       p0 = Point(target.x - xw, yval);
2284       p1 = Point(target.x + xw, yval);
2285       t = (yval - source.y) / direction.y;
2286     } else if (direction.y === 0) {
2287       p0 = Point(xval, target.y - yw);
2288       p1 = Point(xval, target.y + yw);
2289       t = (xval - source.x) / direction.x;
2290     } else {
2291       tX = (xval - source.x) / direction.x;
2292       tY = (yval - source.y) / direction.y;
2293       if ((tX < tY || ((-xw < source.x - target.x) && (source.x - target.x < xw))) && !((-yw < source.y - target.y) && (source.y - target.y < yw))) {
2294         p0 = Point(target.x - xw, yval);
2295         p1 = Point(target.x + xw, yval);
2296         t = tY;
2297       } else {
2298         p0 = Point(xval, target.y - yw);
2299         p1 = Point(xval, target.y + yw);
2300         t = tX;
2301       }
2302     }
2303     if (t > 0) {
2304       areaPQ0 = direction.cross(p0.subtract(source));
2305       areaPQ1 = direction.cross(p1.subtract(source));
2306       return areaPQ0 * areaPQ1 < 0 ? (hit = direction.scale(t).add(source)) : null;
2307     }
2308   }

2312   var REPL, container, input, output, repl, runButton;
2313   REPL = function(input, output) {
2314     var print;
2315     print = function(message) {
2316       return output.append($("<li />", {
2317         text: message
2318       }));
2319     };
2320     return {
2321       run: function() {
2322         var code, result, source;
2323         source = input.val();
2324         try {
2325           code = CoffeeScript.compile(source, {
2326             bare: true
2327           });
2328           if (code.indexOf("var") === 0) {
2329             code = code.substring(code.indexOf("\n"));
2330           }
2331           result = eval(code);
2332           print(" => " + (result));
2333           return input.val('');
2334         } catch (error) {
2335           return error.stack ? print(error.stack) : print(error.toString());
2336         }
2337       }
2338     };
2339   };
2340   container = $("<div />", {
2341     "class": "console"
2342   });
2343   input = $("<textarea />");
2344   output = $("<ul />");
2345   runButton = $("<button />", {
2346     text: "Run"
2347   });
2348   repl = REPL(input, output);
2349   container.append(output).append(input).append(runButton);
2350   return $(function() {
2351     runButton.click(function() {
2352       return repl.run();
2353     });
2354     return $("body").append(container);
2355   });

2357 function DialogBox(I) {
2358   I = I || {};
2359   
2360   $.reverseMerge(I, {
2361     backgroundColor: "#000",
2362     blinkRate: 8,
2363     cursor: true,
2364     cursorWidth: 10,
2365     height: 480,
2366     lineHeight: 16,
2367     paddingX: 24,
2368     paddingY: 24,
2369     text: "",
2370     textColor: "#080",
2371     width: 640,
2372     x: 0,
2373     y: 0
2374   });
2375   
2376   I.textWidth = I.width - 2*(I.paddingX);
2377   I.textHeight = I.height - 2*(I.paddingY);
2378   
2379   var blinkCount = 0;
2380   var cursorOn = true;
2381   
2382   var pageOffset = 0;
2383   var displayChars = 0;
2384   
2385   return {
2386     complete: function() {
2387       return displayChars >= I.text.length - 1;
2388     },
2389     
2390     draw: function(canvas) {
2391       //TODO: A lot of the logic in here should be moved into the
2392       // update method and pre-computed.
2393       var textStart = Point(I.paddingX, I.paddingY + I.lineHeight);
2394       
2395       canvas.withTransform(Matrix.translation(I.x, I.y), function() {
2396         canvas.fillColor(I.backgroundColor);
2397         canvas.fillRect(0, 0, I.width, I.height);
2398         
2399         canvas.fillColor(I.textColor);
2400         
2401         var pageCharCount = 0;
2402         var displayText = I.text.substr(pageOffset, displayChars);
2403         
2404         var piecesRemaining = displayText.split(' ');
2405         var lineWidth = 0;
2406         var line = 0;
2407         
2408         while(piecesRemaining.length > 0) {
2409           var currentLine = piecesRemaining.shift();
2410           
2411           while((canvas.measureText(currentLine) <= I.textWidth) && (piecesRemaining.length > 0)) {
2412             var proposedLine = currentLine + " " + piecesRemaining[0];
2413             
2414             if(canvas.measureText(proposedLine) <= I.textWidth) {
2415               piecesRemaining.shift();
2416               currentLine = proposedLine;
2417             } else {
2418               break;
2419                 ;//NOOP
2420             }
2421           }
2422           
2423           pageCharCount += currentLine.length;
2424           
2425           canvas.fillText(currentLine, textStart.x, textStart.y + line * I.lineHeight);
2426           lineWidth = canvas.measureText(currentLine);
2427           
2428           if(line * I.lineHeight < I.textHeight) {
2429             line += 1;
2430           } else {
2431             pageOffset += pageCharCount + line;
2432             line = 0;
2433             pageCharCount = 0;
2434             displayChars = 0;
2435             break;
2436               ;
2437           }
2438         }
2439         
2440         if(cursorOn && I.cursor) {
2441           canvas.fillRect(textStart.x + lineWidth, textStart.y + (line - 2) *I.lineHeight, I.cursorWidth, I.lineHeight);
2442         }
2443       });
2444       
2445     },
2446     
2447     flush: function() {
2448       displayChars = I.text.length;
2449     },
2450     
2451     setText: function(text) {
2452       pageOffset = 0;
2453       displayChars = 0;
2454       I.text = text;
2455     },
2456     
2457     update: function() {
2458       displayChars += 1;
2459       blinkCount += 1;
2460       
2461       if(blinkCount >= I.blinkRate) {
2462         blinkCount = 0;
2463         cursorOn = !cursorOn;
2464       }
2465     }
2466   };
2467 };
2468 var Drawable;
2469 /**
2470 The Drawable module is used to provide a simple draw method to the including
2471 object.
2472 
2473 @name Drawable
2474 @constructor
2475 @param {Object} I Instance variables
2476 */
2477 Drawable = function(I) {
2478   I || (I = {});

2480     color: "#196",

2482   });

2486       return (I.height = sprite.height);
2487     });
2488   }
2489   return {
2490     /**
2491     Draw this object on the canvas. It uses the x and y instance attributes to position
2492     and the sprite instance attribute to determine what to draw.
2493 
2494     @name draw
2495     @methodOf Drawable#
2496 
2497     @param canvas
2498     */
2499     draw: function(canvas) {
2500       if (I.transform) {
2501         return canvas.withTransform(Matrix.translation(I.x + I.width / 2, I.y + I.height / 2).concat(I.transform).concat(Matrix.translation(-I.width / 2, -I.height / 2)), function(canvas) {
2502           if (I.sprite) {
2503             return I.sprite.draw(canvas, 0, 0);
2504           } else if (I.color) {
2505             canvas.fillColor(I.color);
2506             return canvas.fillRect(0, 0, I.width, I.height);
2507           }
2508         });
2509       } else {
2510         if (I.sprite) {
2511           return I.sprite.draw(canvas, I.x, I.y);
2512         } else if (I.color) {
2513           canvas.fillColor(I.color);
2514           return canvas.fillRect(I.x, I.y, I.width, I.height);
2515         }
2516       }
2517     }
2518   };

2540 Emitterable = function(I, self) {
2541   var n, particles;
2542   I || (I = {});
2543   $.reverseMerge(I, {
2544     batchSize: 1,
2545     emissionRate: 1,
2546     color: "blue",
2547     width: 0,
2548     height: 0,
2549     generator: {},
2550     particleCount: Infinity,
2551     particleData: {
2552       acceleration: Point(0, 0.1),
2553       age: 0,
2554       color: "blue",
2555       duration: 30,
2556       height: 2,
2557       maxSpeed: 2,
2558       offset: Point(0, 0),
2559       sprite: false,
2560       spriteName: false,
2561       velocity: Point(-0.25, 1),
2562       width: 2
2563     }
2564   });
2565   particles = [];
2566   n = 0;
2567   return {
2568     before: {
2569       draw: function(canvas) {
2570         return particles.invoke("draw", canvas);
2571       },
2572       update: function() {
2573         I.batchSize.times(function() {
2574           var center, particleProperties;
2575           if (n < I.particleCount && rand() < I.emissionRate) {
2576             center = self.center();
2577             particleProperties = $.reverseMerge({
2578               x: center.x,
2579               y: center.y
2580             }, I.particleData);
2581             $.each(I.generator, function(key, value) {
2582               return I.generator[key].call ? (particleProperties[key] = I.generator[key](n, I)) : (particleProperties[key] = I.generator[key]);
2583             });
2584             particleProperties.x += particleProperties.offset.x;
2585             particleProperties.y += particleProperties.offset.y;
2586             particles.push(GameObject(particleProperties));
2587             return n += 1;
2588           }
2589         });
2590         particles = particles.select(function(particle) {
2591           return particle.update();
2592         });
2593         return n === I.particleCount && !particles.length ? (I.active = false) : null;
2594       }
2595     }
2596   };

2791 var GameObject;
2792 GameObject = function(I) {
2793   var autobindEvents, defaultModules, modules, self;
2794   I || (I = {});
2795   $.reverseMerge(I, {
2796     age: 0,
2797     active: true,
2798     created: false,
2799     destroyed: false,
2800     x: 0,
2801     y: 0,
2802     width: 8,
2803     height: 8,
2804     solid: false,
2805     includedModules: [],
2806     excludedModules: []
2807   });
2808   self = Core(I).extend({
2809     update: function() {
2810       if (I.active) {
2811         self.trigger('step');
2812         I.age += 1;
2813       }
2814       return I.active;
2815     },
2816     draw: $.noop,
2817     position: function() {
2818       return Point(I.x, I.y);
2819     },
2820     collides: function(bounds) {
2821       return Collision.rectangular(I, bounds);
2822     },
2823     destroy: function() {
2824       if (!(I.destroyed)) {
2825         self.trigger('destroy');
2826       }
2827       I.destroyed = true;
2828       return (I.active = false);
2829     }
2830   });
2831   defaultModules = [Bindable, Bounded, Drawable, Durable, Movable];
2832   modules = defaultModules.concat(I.includedModules.invoke('constantize'));
2833   modules = modules.without(I.excludedModules.invoke('constantize'));
2834   modules.each(function(Module) {
2835     return self.include(Module);
2836   });
2837   self.attrAccessor("solid");
2838   autobindEvents = ['create', 'destroy', 'step'];
2839   autobindEvents.each(function(eventName) {
2840     var event;
2841     return (event = I[eventName]) ? (typeof event === "function" ? self.bind(eventName, event) : self.bind(eventName, eval("(function(self) {" + (event) + "})"))) : null;
2842   });
2843   if (!(I.created)) {
2844     self.trigger('create');
2845   }
2846   I.created = true;
2847   $(document).bind('mousedown', function(event) {
2848     return ((I.x <= event.offsetX) && (event.offsetX <= I.x + I.width)) && ((I.y <= event.offsetY) && (event.offsetY <= I.y + I.height)) ? self.trigger('click') : null;
2849   });
2850   return self;
2851 };
